         <div type="translation" resp="#jmr" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Statue of</supplied> Liber Pater, son of Jupiter, the offering which I had destined for the Lar of the home city of Severus, the son of Jupiter, 
               who is my sun, my father Pudens <supplied reason="subaudible">paid</supplied> on behalf of his son, on account of my candidature for the tribunate 
               <supplied reason="subaudible">at Rome</supplied> and my subsequent praetorship and the great indulgence which the two <foreign xml:lang="la">principes</foreign> 
               have conferred on us; as an offering which comprises all that I have vowed I dedicate two elephant tusks from your own Indian animals.</p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Line 8. Severus and Caracalla, from 196</p>
